# 🎨 Frontend README (`React + Vite Dashboard`)

```md
# HX Shopify Headless Frontend

A modern React dashboard to interact with Shopify Headless Backend APIs.

---

## 🚀 Features

- Product listing dashboard
- Storefront search
- Collection browsing
- API integration with backend
- Clean dashboard UI
- React state-driven architecture

---

## 🧰 Tech Stack

- React 18+
- Vite
- TypeScript (optional)
- Axios / Fetch API
- Tailwind CSS (or custom CSS)

---

## 📁 Project Structure
src/
components/
pages/
services/
hooks/
App.tsx
main.tsx


---

## ⚙️ Setup

### 1. Install dependencies

```bash
npm install
2. Configure API URL

Create .env file:

VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
3. Run frontend
npm run dev

App will run at:

http://localhost:5173
🔌 Backend Connection

Frontend communicates with backend via:

const API_URL = import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL;

Example API call:

fetch(`${API_URL}/products`)
📊 Features Breakdown
🛍 Products Dashboard
Displays Shopify products
Supports pagination (if implemented)
🔎 Search
GET /search?q=shirt

Search is optional for other endpoints.

📦 Collections

Displays grouped product categories

🎨 UI Improvements (Recommended)
Add Tailwind CSS
Add loading skeletons
Add product cards grid
Add filters (price, tags)
Add search debounce
🧪 Environment Variables
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
🐞 Common Issues
Backend not connecting
Check CORS in backend
Verify API URL in .env
Empty response
Ensure backend is running
Check Shopify token validity
🚀 Build for Production
npm run build
